</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C644D59650FC13BFECEFA6DFDA1BEC1" authority="Lourenco &amp; Duhem, 2009" authorityName="Lourenco &amp; Duhem" authorityYear="2009" box="[340,607,1434,1460]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Pantobuthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="complicatus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B910EAC8650FC13BFECEFA6DFDA1BEC1" box="[340,607,1434,1460]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Pantobuthus complicatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22357B3650FC13BFDFDFA6DFD5ABEC1" box="[615,676,1434,1460]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37E6551650FC134FF23FA4AFBAABA8B" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="45" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BDB36DA650FC13BFF23FA4AFBADBDFD" blockId="7.[140,1108,800,1672]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis id="B910EAC8650FC13BFF23FA4AFE05BEA2" bold="true" box="[185,507,1469,1495]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Affinities of the new genus.</emphasis>
The new genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C644D59650FC13BFD2BFA4AFCC8BEA2" authorityName="Lourenco &amp; Duhem" authorityYear="2009" box="[689,822,1469,1495]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Pantobuthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B910EAC8650FC13BFD2BFA4AFCC8BEA2" box="[689,822,1469,1495]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Pantobuthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shows affinities with several genera, such as 
<taxonomicName id="4C644D59650FC13BFEE2FA17FDEFBE8F" authorityName="Vachon" authorityYear="1950" box="[376,529,1504,1530]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Odontobuthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B910EAC8650FC13BFEE2FA17FDEFBE8F" box="[376,529,1504,1530]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Odontobuthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C644D59650FC13BFDBEFA17FD91BE8F" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[548,623,1504,1530]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B910EAC8650FC13BFDBEFA17FD91BE8F" box="[548,623,1504,1530]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Buthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C644D59650FC13BFD1BFA17FD01BE8F" authorityName="Vachon" authorityYear="1950" box="[641,767,1504,1530]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Mesobuthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B910EAC8650FC13BFD1BFA17FD01BE8F" box="[641,767,1504,1530]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Mesobuthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C644D59650FC13BFC8BFA16FC72BE8F" authorityName="Birula" authorityYear="1908" box="[785,908,1505,1530]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Hottentotta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B910EAC8650FC13BFC8BFA16FC72BE8F" box="[785,908,1505,1530]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Hottentotta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C644D59650FC13BFC57FA17FBB2BE8F" authorityName="Levy, Amitai &amp; Shulov" authorityYear="1973" box="[973,1100,1504,1530]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Vachoniolus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B910EAC8650FC13BFC57FA17FBB2BE8F" box="[973,1100,1504,1530]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Vachoniolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which are also elements of the North African and Palaearctic faunas. The moderately marked carapace carinae which form only an incomplete ‘lyra’ configuration associates the new genus to 
<taxonomicName id="4C644D59650FC13BFEC3F9BCFE2ABD11" authorityName="Birula" authorityYear="1908" box="[345,468,1611,1636]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Hottentotta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B910EAC8650FC13BFEC3F9BCFE2ABD11" box="[345,468,1611,1636]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Hottentotta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C644D59650FC13BFD8AF9BDFD70BD11" authorityName="Vachon" authorityYear="1950" box="[528,654,1610,1636]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Mesobuthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B910EAC8650FC13BFD8AF9BDFD70BD11" box="[528,654,1610,1636]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Mesobuthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but metasomal segments II to IV with strong spinoid granules on the ventral carinae, are more similar to those of the genus
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDB36DA6500C134FF16FF50FBADBA5F" blockId="8.[140,1108,167,510]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">
<taxonomicName id="4C644D596500C134FF16FF50FEDBBBB4" authorityName="Vachon" authorityYear="1950" box="[140,293,167,193]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Odontobuthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B910EAC86500C134FF16FF50FEDBBBB4" box="[140,293,167,193]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">Odontobuthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Th e very central position of the median ocular tubercle on the carapace and the shape of the telson with a strongly globular vesicle and a very short aculeus associates 
<taxonomicName id="4C644D596500C134FF64FF1AFE7DBA72" authority="Lourenco &amp; Duhem, 2009" authorityName="Lourenco &amp; Duhem" authorityYear="2009" box="[254,387,237,263]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Pantobuthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis id="B910EAC86500C134FF64FF1AFE7DBA72" box="[254,387,237,263]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">Pantobuthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22357B36500C134FE16FF19FE24BA7D" box="[396,474,238,264]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
with 
<taxonomicName id="4C644D596500C134FDBAFF1AFD95BA72" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[544,619,237,263]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B910EAC86500C134FDBAFF1AFD95BA72" box="[544,619,237,263]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">Buthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In this last genus, however, both carapace and mesosomal carinae are strongly developed and the ‘lyra’ configuration is totally
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDB36DA6500C134FF16FEC4FBAABA8B" blockId="8.[140,1108,167,510]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">
complete. Th e very short and bulky pedipalps again associate 
<taxonomicName id="4C644D596500C134FCA5FEC4FC3ABA38" authority="Lourenco &amp; Duhem, 2009" authorityName="Lourenco &amp; Duhem" authorityYear="2009" box="[831,964,307,333]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Pantobuthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis id="B910EAC86500C134FCA5FEC4FC3ABA38" box="[831,964,307,333]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">Pantobuthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22357B36500C134FC56FEC3FBE7BA3B" box="[972,1049,308,334]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
with 
<taxonomicName id="4C644D596500C134FF16FEA0FF29BA04" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[140,215,343,369]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B910EAC86500C134FF16FEA0FF29BA04" box="[140,215,343,369]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">Buthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the very strongly globular chela recall those of the male 
<taxonomicName id="4C644D596500C134FC57FEA0FBB2BA04" authorityName="Levy, Amitai &amp; Shulov" authorityYear="1973" box="[973,1100,343,369]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Vachoniolus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B910EAC86500C134FC57FEA0FBB2BA04" box="[973,1100,343,369]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">Vachoniolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The male of 
<taxonomicName id="4C644D596500C134FE8FFE8DFDE5BAE1" authority="Lourenco &amp; Duhem, 2009" authorityName="Lourenco &amp; Duhem" authorityYear="2009" box="[277,539,378,404]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Pantobuthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="complicatus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B910EAC86500C134FE8FFE8DFDE5BAE1" box="[277,539,378,404]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">Pantobuthus complicatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22357B36500C134FDB8FE8DFDA3BAE1" box="[546,605,378,404]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
remains unknown. Finally, the total displacement of chela trichobothrium 
<emphasis id="B910EAC86500C134FE70FE6AFDF7BAC2" bold="true" box="[490,521,413,439]" pageId="8" pageNumber="45">db</emphasis>
to the internal surface of fixed finger, the retreated position of lateral eyes and the tarsi with two series of short spine-like setae, but with external series reduced or totally absent appear to be particular characteristics of this genus.
</paragraph>
